**Director of Accounting, Planning & Customer Service**

**General Responsibilities**

As a member of the Water Authority’s management team, is responsible for the accounting, information systems, customer billing, customer service, and field customer service functions of the Water Authority. This position’s responsibilities include assuring that these functions attain the corporate goals and objectives for which it is responsible in a timely and efficient manner.

**Specific Responsibilities**

· Provide excellent customer service at all times;

· Direct and oversee the operation of accounting, customer billing, customer service and field customer service functions;

· Direct and review the preparation of all reporting of monthly, quarterly, annual and other periodic financial results to assure timeliness and accuracy;

· Prepare, consolidate and review all operating plans and forecasts; support in the preparation of annual capital plan;

· Explain or obtain accurate explanations of all material variances from forecasts and report these variances to the Water Authority’s Board of Directors in a timely and efficient manner;

· Prepare accurate long range forecasts of revenue requirements from which to develop a prudent financial strategy plan;

· Oversee the customer billing and accounts receivable functions to assure accurate and timely billing and recording of receivables, including the monitoring of the collection program;

· Support the Water Authority’s Superintendent as required;

· Participate in the Audit & Finance Subcommittee of the Board of Directors;

· Participate in Revenue Bond Finances;

· Maintain appropriate responsibility area employee communications;

· Prepare accurate periodic cash flow projections from which to manage cash flow efficiently;

· Participate in or direct the development of Water Authority accounting policy and administer approved accounting procedures;

· Assist other management team members in achieving their goals and objectives;

· Become familiar with the Water Authority’s customer information systems.

· Develop utility rates and tariffs commensurate with annual board approved operating and capital budget.

· Provide statistical support and forecasts for long-term bond financing requirements.

**Qualifications** 

· Bachelor’s degree in accounting;

· Five or more years of general accounting experience, including supervisory experience;

· Knowledge of financial reporting including generally accepted accounting principles, Governmental Accounting Standards Board statements and interpretations, and all federal, state and local reporting requirements;

· Must be proficient in the utilization of the Microsoft software products in a Windows environment;

· Experience in preparation of capital and operating plans and other long range strategic plans;

· Ability to work cooperatively with others;

· Good verbal and written communication skills;

· Ability to deal with outside third parties to achieve goals of Water Authority.

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: $148,000.00 - $180,000.00 per year

Benefits:

* Dental insurance
* Disability insurance
* Employee assistance program
* Health insurance
* Life insurance
* Paid time off
* Retirement plan
* Vision insurance

Physical Setting:

* Office

Schedule:

* 8 hour shift

Work Location: In person

Paul Hastings is a leading international law firm that provides innovative legal solutions to many of the world's top financial institutions and Fortune Global 500 companies. With a strong presence throughout Asia, Europe, Latin America, and the U.S., we have the global reach and extensive capabilities to provide personalized service wherever our clients’ needs take us. As one of the world’s leading law firms, we seek dynamic individuals who share our commitment to service, innovation, and professional growth.


We have an opening for a Practice Manager – Real Estate.


The Practice Manager will support the leaders of the Real Estate Department at the Firm. The Practice Manager will work alongside the designated Practice/Department Chairs and other business operations departments (i.e., Finance, Talent, Business Development, Practice Innovation, IT, Communications, etc.) to ensure operational efficiency, develop, drive, and execute their strategic plan, provide and manage financial insights, handle work allocation and staffing, support client value initiatives, and otherwise support the practice’s business needs and operations. As a trusted advisor and “chief of staff” to the practice leaders, the Practice Manager is a highly collaborative self-starter, with demonstrated experience, confidence, and professionalism in communicating with partners, management, and timekeepers at all levels of the organization.


The Practice Manager will report to the chairs of the Real Estate Department with a reporting line to the Director of Practice Management, sitting within the Practice Innovation Department.


In this capacity, the Practice Manager will:


* Collaborate with the Director of Practice Management, PG Chairs, partners, other business operations departments, and other stakeholders to facilitate the development and relentless execution of Practice Group strategic plans with clear and achievable goals focused on revenue, profitability, headcount, reputation, brand awareness, profile and competitive differentiation;
* Collaborate with Finance Department to analyze Practice Group financials and other key performance indicators to stay on top of all timekeeper hours, performance trends, and overall practice revenue, providing actionable insights towards the management of the Practice;
* Collaborate with Talent Department to manage a productive workforce where: work assignments are provided efficiently and equitably; opportunities are allocated in accordance with Practice Group and individual development goals; performance issues are identified early and addressed; and Practice Group size is adjusted to meet projected workflow demands;
* Collaborate with business operations departments to facilitate and coordinate lateral attorney onboarding efforts;
* Manage the daily execution of business needs / operations of the assigned Practice Groups, including developing and managing the Practice operations budget, establishing a consistent framework for Practice Group meetings and communications, supporting Firm processes like billing and collections, matter intake and matter type classifications, and follow-up on initiatives / action items, etc.;
* Enhance the experience for top clients by serving as a point of contact for the in-house legal operations team to improve the overall engagement and efficient delivery of legal services;
* Collaborate regularly with colleagues in Practice Innovation and across other administrative departments to continue to drive efficiencies, process improvement, and innovation throughout the Practice Groups and across the Firm; and
* Support Practice Chairs with the daily operations of the group, including preparing for PG meetings and retreats.

In addition, the Practice Manager will be expected to have:


* Strong business acumen and analytical skills; the ability to develop and successfully execute comprehensive project and operational plans from broadly stated objectives;
* Proven experience driving continuous improvement and innovation in business operations, technology, infrastructure, and practices in a complex, matrixed, global professional services;
* Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to deal effectively with lawyers and staff at all levels of the organization and to regularly handle sensitive and confidential information;
* Advanced understanding of business operations and proficiency in financial performance metrics;
* Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite, including specifically Excel, Word, PowerPoint, Project and Visio;
* Strong project management and organizational skills, including ability to plan and facilitate at group and individual levels;
* Ability to handle a wide variety of responsibilities and work in a fast-paced environment;
* Ability to solve problems and provide solutions, take initiative, and work independently in high-pressure situations;
* Excellent oral and written communication skills;
* Demonstrated confidence and competence in dealing with individuals in leadership positions; and
* Strong work ethic and desire to lead and achieve at a high standard of excellence.

Qualifications:


* Bachelor’s degree (required); JD or MBA (preferred);
* A minimum of 5 years’ experience serving as a practicing lawyer or business professional with an emphasis on practice management and operations (required); and
* Experience working with real estate or transactional practices (preferred).

Employees will be provided with an excellent career opportunity in a collaborative environment, in addition to a generous total compensation package with the opportunity to earn bonuses based on individual contribution and firm profitability.


The salary wage range that we expect to pay for this position is a minimum of $150,700 and a maximum of $196,400 annually. The actual pay wage may vary based on experience or other relevant factors.


Eligible employees can participate in the Firm’s comprehensive benefits program, which include the following:


* Medical, Dental, Vision, Life/AD&D, Long Term Care, and Short and Long Term Disability
* Flexible Spending Account and Health Savings Account
* Healthcare Concierge and Advocacy
* Voluntary 401k Plan and Profit Sharing
* 10 Paid Holidays per year and a generous PTO program
* Family Support including Pediatric Mental Health and Parental Support, Paid Parental Leave, Fertility Benefits, and Breast Milk Shipping
* Back-up Child Care, Elder Care, and Tutoring
* Wellness Programs (Employee Assistance Program, Mental Health, and Well-Being Events)
* Retirement Plan Consulting
* Anniversary Bonus Program
* Professional Development Programs
* Transportation Allowance and Commuter Benefits
* International Travel Insurance
* Auto/Home/Legal Insurance
* Pet Insurance
* Employee discounts
* And more!

The Firm has a range of diversity initiatives including our Paul Hastings Affinity Networks (PHANs), Women’s Initiative, and PH Balanced. These initiatives provide a firmwide forum to share experiences, as well as an opportunity to participate in a supportive network with common interests to help make life at the firm more inclusive. Learn more about our Global Diversity, Inclusion and Wellness Initiatives here.


